body.p:
The speech situation of experiencing fear having seen the path; averting the coming; 
    the speech situation of desolation on account of the guarding; saying ‘you come either in the day or night’; 
    saying ‘do not come’ and saying ‘I knew this woman as being honouratble today’ - the poet-scholars say 
    all of these such [situations] are ‘asking for marriage’.
